那意味着你是那个人的继承人。

163
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:19,920
That's right.
没错。

164
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:20,920
Okay.
好的。

165
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:24,480
Or in his inheritance, he received a large house.
或者在他的遗产中，他得到了一栋大房子。

166
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,880
He was the heir to a great fortune.
他是一笔巨大财富的继承人。

167
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:28,400
Okay, interesting.
好的，有意思。

168
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:32,880
So again, inheritance wasn't in the dialogue but I think it's worth mentioning.
所以再说一次，遗产这个词在对话中没有出现，但我认为值得提一下。

169
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:39,120
And I think now we can move on to four very interesting items that we have for you on
而且我认为现在我们可以继续讲四个非常有趣的条目，这些是我们为你们准备的

170
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,440
Fluency Builder.
流利度提升部分。

171
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:46,760
Okay, these first two are words that we normally read or hear in legal documents.
好的，前两个词是我们通常在法律文件中读到或听到的。

172
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:51,520
And I want to place emphasis on the fact that we don't really say them in spoken English.
我想强调一个事实，我们在口语中并不真的说这些词。

173
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:55,520
So remember that these are more formal terms.
所以记住这些是更正式的术语。

174
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:58,440
The first one is hereby.
第一个是“特此”。

175
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:01,120
I hereby declare.
我特此宣布。

176
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:03,280
That means now.
那意思是“现在”。

177
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:08,800
With this word, with this spoken sentence, this will happen.
通过这个词，通过这个说出的句子，这件事将会发生。

178
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:11,160
I think we've seen it like in movies sometimes.
我想我们有时在电影里见过它。

179
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:14,800
I hereby declare this country in the name of England.
我特此以英格兰的名义宣布这片土地。

180
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:17,320
I hereby declare you man and wife.
我特此宣布你们结为夫妻。

181
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,320
Exactly.
正是。

182
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,320
Okay.
好的。

183
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:21,280
That means in this moment, this happens.
那意思是此刻，这件事发生。

184
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,280
Okay.
好的。

185
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:26,600
And a very similar word that we also saw in the dialogue is herewith.
还有一个非常相似的词，我们在对话中也看到了，就是“随函”。

186
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:32,680
So in the Will and Testament, we hear Luke Thompson who says, I herewith affix my signature.
所以在遗嘱中，我们听到卢克·汤普森说：“我随函附上我的签名。”

187
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:40,600
That means with the action of signing my name, signing my signature, this will be completed.
那意思是随着签名的动作，签署我的名字，这件事将完成。

188
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:43,880
So I herewith, you have to have an action, not just a word.
所以“我随函”，你必须有一个动作，而不仅仅是一个词。

189
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:44,880
Okay.
好的。

190
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,600
So I herewith.
所以我随函。

191
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:49,960
I herewith attach my seal.
我随函附上我的印章。

192
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:52,160
A seal is like a stamp.
印章就像图章一样。

193
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:55,000
Very common in the old days when you had real letters.
在过去有实体信件的时候非常常见。

194
00:09:55,000 --> 00:10:00,880
But I herewith attach my seal and give my approval to this document.
但我随函附上我的印章，并批准这份文件。

195
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:01,880
Okay.
好的。

196
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:03,200
So it has to be something physical.
所以它必须是某种物理的东西。

197
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,200
Yeah.
是的。

198
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,200
Right.
对。

199
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:09,360
So if maybe you're writing like this very classic letter and you say, I herewith include
所以如果你在写一封非常经典的信，你说：“我随函附上

200
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,360
a lock of my hair.
一缕我的头发。”

201
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:11,360
Oh, how romantic.
哦，真浪漫。

202
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,360
Okay.
好的。

203
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,360
That's kind of creepy.
那有点吓人。

204
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:17,880
But you're including or attaching physically, right?
但你是物理地附上或包含，对吧？

205
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:21,160
I guess the modern version of herewith would be attach.
我想“随函”的现代版本就是“附件”。

206
00:10:21,160 --> 00:10:22,160
Yeah.
是的。

207
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:23,160
Okay.
好的。

208
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:24,160
Good.
很好。

209
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:25,160
Herewith, hereby.
“随函”，“特此”。

210
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:29,160
We've got another phrase here that you might hear more commonly.
我们这里还有另一个短语，你可能更常听到。

211
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:33,360
The beginning of the Will and Testament, there's a phrase as follows.
遗嘱的开头有一个短语“如下”。

212
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,520
Okay.
好的。

213
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:38,400
I direct that the disposition of my remains be as follows.
我指示我的遗体处置如下。

214
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:41,800
So with my body do as follows.
所以对我的身体做如下处理。

215
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:49,160
So basically this is a very common way of putting this in a sentence to indicate that
所以基本上这是一种非常常见的在句子中表达的方式，用来表示

216
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:51,840
you're going to start to list items.
你要开始列举项目。

217
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,840
That's right.
没错。

218
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:53,840
Or give instructions.
或者给出指示。

219
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:54,840
Give instructions.
给出指示。

220
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:57,760
So for example, to make a loaf of bread, do as follows.
所以例如，要做一条面包，请按如下步骤操作。

221
00:10:57,760 --> 00:11:00,080
Number one, get some flour.
第一，拿一些面粉。

222
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,640
Number two, add some water.
第二，加一些水。

223
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:06,600
So this is a way for us to say, listen, I'm going to give you instructions or a list.
所以这是一种方式，让我们说：“听着，我要给你指示或列表。

224
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,600
Pay attention.
注意听。”

225
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:10,300
So please do as follows.
所以请按如下步骤操作。

226
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:11,840
Please act as follows.
请按如下方式行动。

227
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:12,840
Okay.
好的。

228
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:13,840
Very good.
非常好。

229
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:19,920
And our last word that we have here, going back to herewith, he said, I herewith affix
我们这里的最后一个词，回到“随函”，他说：“我随函

230
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:21,040
my signature.
附上我的签名。”

231
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:22,520
What does it mean when you affix?
“附上”是什么意思？

232
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:23,520
Okay.
好的。

233
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:29,840
Affix is a word we have a number of other words for these days, so you rarely hear it.
“附上”这个词我们现在有很多其他词可以替代，所以你很少听到它。

234
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:32,280
It means to attach or to include.
它的意思是“附加”或“包含”。

235
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:33,280
Okay.
好的。

236
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:36,320
So I herewith affix my signature would be attach my signature.
所以“我随函附上我的签名”就是“附加我的签名”。

237
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,320
Right.
对。

238
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:43,920
I herewith provide my signature or I herewith affix my address or I herewith affix something.
我随函提供我的签名，或者我随函附上我的地址，或者我随函附上某物。

239
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:44,920
Okay.
好的。

240
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:45,920
Very good.
非常好。

241
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,320
Really interesting stuff.
真是有趣的内容。

242
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:53,640
You'll obviously see this very commonly with legal documents such as these, even though
你显然会经常在像这样的法律文件中看到这种用法，尽管

